8.962 | General Relativity | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/physics/8-962-general-relativity-spring-2006 | level:Graduate instructors:Prof. Edmund Bertschinger, Prof. Scott Hughes features: textbook:Spacetime and Geometry: An Introduction to General Relativity (Carroll, Sean B.) prereq:18.03 18.06 8.07 description:The basic principles of Einstein's general theory of relativity, differential geometry, experimental tests of general relativity, black holes, and cosmology. 
